script.py [mode]

mode: 	--help to display this

	-annotation <input dir/file> <annotation source> <output_folder>

		<input dir/file> can be either a bed file or a directory 
		with bed files

		<annotation source> can be any valid file used by bedtools 
		or you can download it now to download, you have four options 
		by now: gcode_hg19 gcode_hg20 ncbi_hg19 ncbi_hg20 just write 
		i.e -download:gcode_hg19

		<output_folder> is the name of a dir where the results will be dumped

	-tsver 	<input dir/file>

		<input dir/file> can be either a bed file or a directory 
		with annotated files from annotation mode to be transformed
		into a tsv to be easier to scan visually




